Code EMFOL
) The Employee Plans Master File On-line (Command Code EMFOL) system provides read only access to Employee Plans Master File data. Scope and (
) Purpose: This IRM section provides the instructions for the use of Data Retrieval System (IDRS) command code EMFOL to display Employee Plans Master File data. (
) Audience: Wage & Investment (W&I), Large Business and International (LB&I), Small Business Self-Employed (SB/SE), Tax Exempt and Entities (TE/GE). (
) Policy Owner: Tax Exempt and Government Entities (TE/GE). (
) Program Owner: Tax Exempt and Government Entities (TE/GE) (
) Primary Stakeholders: Wage & Investment (W&I), Large Business and national (LB&I), Small Business Self-Employed (SB/SE), Tax Exempt and Government Entities (TE/GE). (
) Program Goals: The information provided in this IRM will instruct the user how to access the Employee Plans Master File data (Command Code screen that is requested. (

) The Employee Plans Master File on-line system provides read only access accounts on the Employee Plans Master File (EPMF) in Martinsburg, WV. Information for EPMF accounts are available on-line. Code EMFOL (

) This command code is provided to furnish access to the Employee Plans Master File. Fields available include basic identifying information, amounts, Code EMFOL counts, dates, codes and indicators. Transaction posting and status history also available. Additionally, for any speciﬁed account (EIN), a plan and module index can be requested. (
) Entity, Plan and Tax data are available on-line. (
) A help feature provides on-line information regarding the correct input for the command code. (

) Whenever possible, the entire set of requested data will be presented on a single page (screen). When all requested data cannot ﬁt on a single page, multiple pages will be formatted for the presentation of the entire set of After the initial request, users may page through a multiple page response without re-entering their entry code. ) Abbreviated input formats permit the user to display related data without tering a full command code. (
) The cursor is shown as a “gray box” and will be returned on line
, ready a request for the next screen. (
) Fields that may be negative will be noted on the screen display with a “_”.

) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “C”, and a Last Reported EIN will result in display of all the DLNs, EINs, plans, tax periods and last reported plans input Last Reported EIN (no Plan Number or Tax Period). (
) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “D”, an EIN and a Plan Number will result in display of Plan Administrator data for the speciﬁed EIN/Plan Number (no Period). (

) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “E” and an EIN will result in the display of Entity information including the sponsor/employer name and address as as indicators, codes, notice information and posted transactions for the speciﬁed account (no Plan Number or Tax Period). (
) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “H” will result in the display of an on-line screen. (
) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “I” and an EIN will result in the display of an index of all the plans and their related tax modules for the input EIN (no Number or Tax Period). (
) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “L”, an EIN and Plan Number will result in display of the plan module information as well as posted plan transactions Tax Period). (
) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “S”, an EIN, Plan Number and Tax Period result in the display of the status history of the speciﬁed tax module. (
) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “T”, an EIN Plan Number and Tax Period will result in the display of the tax module data from posted transactions for speciﬁed account. (

) CC EMFOL input with deﬁner “X”, an EIN will result in the display of the Reference EINs (no Plan Number or Tax Period). An EIN Plan Number will result in the display of the Cross Reference EINs and Cross Reference Numbers (no Tax Period).

Full Tax Module Data

Use this format of the Command Code input screen to obtain a display of EPMF Master File data (Tax Module or Status History data). Access to each screen of the display will require input of a command code. Once a particular module is displayed, other pages can be accessed using the CC EMFPG displayed on line 24 of all responses that can have more than one page. See line 24 of displays for deﬁners E, I, L, S and T.
Exhibit 2.3.64-2 (01-14-2007) Command Code EMFOL Input Display

Use this format of the Command Code input screen to obtain a display of EPMF Master File Plan, Ad- ministrator and Cross Reference data. Once a particular Entity module is displayed, other pages can be accessed using the CC EMFPG displayed on line 24. The Administrator and Cross Reference data response is a single page response.
EIN = nn-nnnnnnn
Entity Module or Index or Cross Reference Data

Use this format of the Command Code to obtain a display of EPMF Master File Entity data, Index, Cross Reference and Last Reported Data. Once a particular Entity module or Index or Cross or Last Reported Data is displayed, other pages can be accessed using the CC EMFPG displayed line 24. The Cross Reference data response is a single page response.
